                            Severus 
                            called 
                            Anatolius
                            a false prophet.
                         <a href="/3109-20" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Events</h3><p class="indent">
                            Anatolius prophesied the death of those
                            who communed with non-Chalcedonians who accepted the Henotikon even though it did 
                            not anathematize Chalcedon. He was forced to repent when his prophecies did not come true.
                        
                                The following factoids deal with the closely related events: 3109-19, 3109-18 3109-17.
                             <a href="/3109-18" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">
                            Severus healed a man with boils who thought he was
                            going to die because Anatolius prophesied the death of those
                            who communed with non-Chalcedonians who accepted the Henotikon even though it did 
                            not anathematize Chalcedon.
                        
                                The following factoids deal with the closely related events: 3109-19, 3109-18 3109-17.
                             <a href="/3109-19" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">
                            Anatolius told lies about 
                            Hosius.
